So I’ve never done a sponsored post before but I’ve researched and tested these @truwomen bars and feel like I can give you an honest review.
.
.
.
First- planning what I’m going to eat consumes a ridiculous amount of my time because of all the foods that I avoid (No gluten! No gmo! No canola oil! No xylitol or erythritol! And many many more). I oscillate between eating keto and paleo. When I’m eating paleo I need snacks that I can bring with me to work or while traveling. Most protein bars contain inflammatory ingredients and so I usually avoid them. But I can sign off on the ingredients in these, and the carbohydrate profile is low enough that I could make these work even in ketosis.
.
.
.
Second- they taste great. Obviously an important factor. They’re not chalky or too crumbly, the consistency is appealing, and they’re not too sweet. I Scream For Orange Cream is our favorite which brings me to...
.
.
.
Third- I keep my kids on a low sugar diet and they are obsessed with these because they think they’re candy bars. I keep them in my backpack and when my kids start fighting in the car (instantly upon entering said car) I give them these and they’re quiet for like three entire minutes! An eternity for parents with multiple kids.
.
.
.
So all in all I’m comfortable recommending these to you guys. Great taste, clean ingredients, guilt free and convenient for stressed out moms with human hurricanes for children. #truwomen
